About
Theatre and dining venue based in London's Docklands, offering a modern take on traditional music hall-style entertainment. Groups and parties welcome. Attracts a younger crowd in the evenings; lunches and "pensioner matinees" available all year round (closed for August). UK Coach award for "Britain's Friendliest Venue".

A Most uplifting experience,the afternoon went by far to quickly .
Mar 2024 • Friends
I was invited to a friends special birthday party at Brick lane .For Afternoon tea and a show .
When we arrived the venue was buzzing ,the place was packed everyone excited for what was about to come .Before the show started we had the most delicious afternoon tea ,consisting of a great selection of tasty sandwiches,scones with Jam and clotted cream .small petit fours and lots of tea and coffee served .
In our case we were drinking champagne,there’s a great wine list if you fancy a tipple .Our hostess was surprised with a beautiful birthday cake and a rendition of Happy Birthday 🥳

Then the show began ,comedy and music mixed , something for everyone sing a longs ,great performers , so very professional we had the most amazing afternoon taken back to years gone by .
I know I will be going back again as I’m told they also do three course lunches and dinners plus the great shows .
So if your a visitor to london or a resident you really must pay a visit it is truly a most uplifting experience.
